Q2) problem link: https://codeforces.com/contest/1624/problem/G
// We can check bit by bit from most significant bit to least .
when you are at 30th bit consider all edges where 30th bit is not set if we can form a tree with this then the overall value will be in worst case (2^30)-1 which is less than 2^30
If it is possible to form a tree by not using 30th bit add it to our variable unSet (this will tell us all the bits that we can neglect) then move to next bit .
// code:
int unSet=0; // Initially none of the bits are unset. If ith bit is unset then make unSet=unSet|(1<<i)
for i = 30 to 0
//try to find the tree by ignoring all the bits in unSet and current bit i.e i
unSet=unSet|(1<<i)
bool ret = findTree(edges,unSet) // this will return whether we can form tree without considering edges having atleast one common bit with unSet.
// ret==true  then we can neglect ith bit else we have to consider it or else we cant form the tree so 
if ret==true as we already set ith bit in unSet no need to add it again
else remove ith bit from unSet unSet=unSet xor (1<<i)

// after the for loop
we now al the bits that we dont have to consider so the result is INT_MAX xor unSet
